ðŸ“Š R Basic Graphs â€“ Cheat Sheet

This guide covers basic plotting functions in R using base R only (no ggplot2 or external libraries).

ðŸ§© 1. Basic Plot Syntax
plot(x, y,
     main = "Main Title",
     xlab = "X-axis Label",
     ylab = "Y-axis Label",
     col = "color",
     pch = symbol,
     type = "plot_type",
     lwd = line_width,
     lty = line_type)

ðŸ”¹ Common Parameters:
Parameter	Description
x, y	Numeric vectors for x and y axes
main	Plot title
xlab, ylab	Labels for X and Y axes
col	Color of points/lines
pch	Point shape (0â€“25), e.g. 16 = filled circle
type	Type of plot: "p" = points, "l" = lines, "b" = both, "o" = overplotted, "h" = histogram lines
lwd	Line width
lty	Line type: 1 = solid, 2 = dashed, 3 = dotted, etc.


-----------------------------------------------------------
barplot(height,
        names.arg = NULL,
        main = NULL,
        xlab = NULL,
        ylab = NULL,
        col = NULL,
        border = NULL,
        horiz = FALSE,
        beside = FALSE,
        ylim = NULL,
        las = 1,
        width = 1,
        space = NULL,
        cex.names = 1,
        cex.axis = 1,
        legend.text = NULL)

| Parameter       | Meaning                                                                                     | Example / Notes                        |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| **height**      | Numeric vector (or matrix) giving the bar heights.                                          | `barplot(c(10, 20, 15))`               |
| **names.arg**   | Labels shown under each bar.                                                                | `names.arg = c("A", "B", "C")`         |
| **main**        | Main title of the plot.                                                                     | `main = "Sales by Product"`            |
| **xlab**        | Label for the x-axis.                                                                       | `xlab = "Products"`                    |
| **ylab**        | Label for the y-axis.                                                                       | `ylab = "Revenue ($)"`                 |
| **col**         | Colors for the bars. Can be one color or a vector.                                          | `col = c("skyblue", "orange", "pink")` |
| **border**      | Border color for bars.                                                                      | `border = "black"`                     |
| **horiz**       | Logical: `TRUE` makes bars horizontal.                                                      | `horiz = TRUE`                         |
| **beside**      | For grouped barplots (when `height` is a matrix). `TRUE` = side-by-side, `FALSE` = stacked. | `beside = TRUE`                        |
| **ylim**        | Range of y-axis values.                                                                     | `ylim = c(0, 50)`                      |
| **las**         | Axis label orientation: <br> `0`=parallel, `1`=horizontal, `2`=perpendicular, `3`=vertical. | `las = 2` makes labels vertical.       |
| **width**       | Relative width of bars.                                                                     | `width = c(1, 0.5, 1.5)`               |
| **space**       | Space between bars.                                                                         | `space = 0.5` (default = 0.2)          |
| **cex.names**   | Size of bar labels.                                                                         | `cex.names = 0.8`                      |
| **cex.axis**    | Size of axis tick labels.                                                                   | `cex.axis = 0.9`                       |
| **legend.text** | Adds a legend (especially useful for grouped bars).                                         | `legend.text = c("2024", "2025")`      |


values <- c(12, 20, 8, 15)
barplot(values,
        names.arg = c("Q1", "Q2", "Q3", "Q4"),
        main = "Quarterly Sales",
        xlab = "Quarter",
        ylab = "Sales (in $K)",
        col = c("skyblue", "orange", "green", "violet"),
        border = "black",
        las = 1,
        ylim = c(0, 25))


-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
pie(x,
    labels = names(x),
    main = NULL,
    col = NULL,
    clockwise = FALSE,
    radius = 1,
    init.angle = 0,
    border = NULL,
    density = NULL,
    angle = 45,
    cex = 1,
    lty = 1)

| Parameter      | Meaning                                                                 | Example / Notes                      |
| -------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| **x**          | Numeric vector â€” values for each slice (usually percentages or counts). | `x = c(30, 20, 25, 25)`              |
| **labels**     | Text labels for each slice.                                             | `labels = c("A", "B", "C", "D")`     |
| **main**       | Main title for the chart.                                               | `main = "Market Share 2025"`         |
| **col**        | Colors for the slices.                                                  | `col = rainbow(4)`                   |
| **clockwise**  | Logical: `TRUE` draws slices clockwise.                                 | `clockwise = TRUE`                   |
| **radius**     | Size of the pie (0â€“1).                                                  | `radius = 0.8` (smaller pie)         |
| **init.angle** | Starting angle (in degrees).                                            | `init.angle = 90` starts at the top. |
| **border**     | Color of slice borders.                                                 | `border = "white"`                   |
| **density**    | Adds shading lines inside slices (number = line density).               | `density = c(10, 20, 30)`            |
| **angle**      | Angle of shading lines (used with `density`).                           | `angle = 45`                         |
| **cex**        | Text size for labels.                                                   | `cex = 0.9`                          |
| **lty**        | Line type for slice borders.                                            | `lty = 2` (dashed lines)             |


share <- c(40, 25, 20, 15)
labels <- c("Product A", "Product B", "Product C", "Product D")

pie(share,
    labels = labels,
    main = "Market Share by Product",
    col = c("red","orange","blue","green"),
    border = "white",
    clockwise = TRUE,
    init.angle = 90,
    cex = 0.9)

